<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3B6A84FB619A821B69B7CA" box="[1181,1385,3291,3320]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="192" pageNumber="954" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alcathoe">Myotis alcathoe</taxonomicName>
and M. hyrcanicus are sister to one another and appear to form a clade basal to the rest of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3B6A84FB3C9B081B18B65C" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1216,1304,3409,3438]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="192" pageNumber="954" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
